{{Quote|I was 11 when I saw ''Return of the Jedi'' in the theater. The one memory that stuck with me the most (even to this day) was when Luke was fighting off the Rancor. Everything about that scene just made me so excited, frightened, and overwhelmed all at the same time. It was the first time a film gave me that rush and will never forget it.|Jason Felix|<ref name="TOS">{{SWArchive|url=eu/explore/profile/f20060803/index.html|text=''Star Wars'' Artist Series: Jason Felix}}</ref>}}
'''Jason Felix''' (born [[1973]]) is an artist who created the cover artwork for the nine ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' novels. He is a self-taught artist who creates digitally manipulated paintings, and he has also done artwork for various video game franchises.<ref name="Simon & Schuster" />

